        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Come home to a great community - Pride Place! Address: 1519-1523 Broadway Seattle, WA 98122 Office Phone: show contact info Beds: Studio / Baths: 1 / Size: 322 - 353 sq ft Monthly Price: $1299 *Optional and usage-based charges not included. Contact office to confirm pricing details and included fees. Capitol Hill has a long history of being a home and cultural center for LGBTQIA+ life in Seattle. Community Roots Housing, in partnership with GenPride, hopes to preserve and enhance this proud tradition by developing LGBTQIA-affirming affordable apartments for seniors in the neighborhood. Pride Place, an eight-story building located on Broadway between Pike and Pine, features 118 apartments above an LGBTQIA-focused community and health services center run by GenPride. Pride Place households must have at least one member aged 55 or older. Deposit: $300 Length of Lease: Call Special Two-month free rent on select units. Please call for details. Property Features: ✓ Bike storage ✓ Ceiling fans in every unit ✓ Community room ✓ Dishwashers in every unit ✓ Shared outdoor patio Apartment Amenities: Pets: Pets as well as emotional support, companion, and service animals are allowed in all Community Roots Housing buildings. Some restrictions may apply to certain types of pets. Site managers can answer detailed questions about pet restrictions. Pet Fee: 25% first months rent or $300 whichever is lower. Please call our Leasing Office for complete Pet Policy information. Business Hours: Mon - Fri: 8:00 AM - 5:00 PM Sat - Sun: - Ready to Lease? Office Phone: show contact info Website: www.apts-rental.com?n=pride_place&rp=nkceDasDuUti&t=wb Online Application: www.apts-rental.com?n=pride_place&rp=nkceDasDuUti&t=ap All pricing, availability, fees, and terms are subject to change without notice. EQUAL HOUSING OPPORTUNITY IVC5DZ0015GDN5K",
