        "geocode_query": "4524 S. Henderson St.",
        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Elizabeth Thomas Homes Leasing Office: 4524 S. Henderson St. Seattle, WA 98118 show contact info Take a look at what Elizabeth Thomas Homes has to offer! Affordable housing conveniently located near light rail station! Elizabeth Thomas Homes is an affordable housing community offering studio, 1-bedroom, 2-bedroom & 3-bedroom apartment homes in addition to a remarkable selection of community amenities designed to enhance your living experience! The clubhouse provides a perfect space for socializing and hosting gatherings, while elevator and disability access ensures inclusivity and convenience for all residents. Our community also features a gated front entry leading to a spacious courtyard and playground area, a computer lab with 6 computers and a printer, and 3 designated laundry facilities, providing a comprehensive package of amenities to cater to your needs and enrich your lifestyle. **Income restrictions apply. Income Restrictions for Elizabeth Thomas Homes # Occupants - Max Income 1 Person - $55,000 1 Person - $66,000 2 People - $62,850 2 People - $75,420 3 People - $70,700 3 People - $84,840 4 People - $78,550 4 People - $94,260 5 People - $84,850 5 People - $101,820 To qualify, the combined annual gross income of a household must be below the maximum annual income amounts listed in the chart. Maximum income limits are based on whether the apartment is a 50% or 60% AMI unit and on the total number of people who will be living in the home. Rental Information: Efficiency Bedroom / 1 Bathroom / 326 - 359 sq ft Monthly Price: $1546 *Optional and usage-based charges not included. Contact office to confirm pricing details and included fees. Apartment Amenities: ✓ Dining Room in Select Units ✓ Kitchen ✓ Oven ✓ Refrigerator ✓ Tub/Shower Additional Information: ✓ Bike Storage ✓ Community Laundry Room ✓ Computer Lab ✓ Income Restrictions Apply ✓ New Construction ✓ On-line Maintenance Request ✓ Playground ✓ Section 42 Welcome ✓ Section 8 Welcome ✓ Smoke Free ✓ 24/7 Resident Portal for Work Orders, Payments & Communicating with the office! ✓ Community room for events, parties etc. ✓ Computer Lab with designated Resident Printer ✓ One block from Rainier Beach light rail station ✓ Rooftop deck with views ✓ Walking distance to schools, grocery, community centers Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/share/1EHgcSwpGz/ Income Restrictions for Elizabeth Thomas Homes # Occupants   -   Max Income       1 Person   -   $63,240       5 People   -   $97,680       2 People   -   $72,300       6 People   -   $104,940       3 People   -   $81,360       7 People   -   $112,080       4 People   -   $90,420       8 People   -   $119,340 To qualify, the combined annual gross (before deductions) income of a household must be below a specific amount. Maximum income limits are based on whether the apartment is a 50% or 60% AMI unit and on the total number of people who will be living in the home. Please contact our friendly Team for more information! Online Application: www.apt-rental.com?n=elizabeth_thomas&rp=24c2Hr6SerJz&t=ap Website: www.apt-rental.com?n=elizabeth_thomas&rp=24c2Hr6SerJz&t=wb Elizabeth Thomas Homes is an Affordable Housing Community participating in the Low-Income Housing Tax Credit (LIHTC) Program, with both 50% and 60% AMI apartment homes. All applicants aged 18 years of age or older must complete their own application and pass our application screening criteria. We must also verify that each household meets all program requirements before they can be approved for move-in by verifying the income, assets, and student statuses for all occupants. Property information, pricing and income limits are current as of 03/15/2025. Rental rates, income limits, unit availability, lease terms, deposits, apartment features, amenities and specials are subject to change without notice. Terms may fluctuate based on qualifying standards. Floorplans and square footages displayed are approximations, and may vary between individual units. Occupancy guidelines may apply, unless otherwise specified. Pricing is valid for new residents only. Please contact the leasing office for more details. EQUAL HOUSING OPPORTUNITY All pricing, availability, fees, and terms are subject to change without notice. EQUAL HOUSING OPPORTUNITY DD7A71A40CA44B0",
