        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Welcome home to Pride Place! Located at: 1519-1523 Broadway Seattle, WA 98122 Rental Information: # of Bedrooms: Studio # of Bathrooms: 1 Square Footage: 322 - 353 sq ft Monthly Price: $1299 *Optional and usage-based charges not included. Contact office to confirm pricing details and included fees. Phone Number: show contact info Welcome to Pride Place, 118 units of affordable housing for seniors 55+ in the heart of Capitol Hill. Located in central Seattle just two blocks from the Capitol Hill light rail station, Pride Place is mere steps away from several grocery stores, First Hill medical centers, a variety of dining options, and green spaces such as Cal Anderson and Volunteer Parks. Pride Place is designed to be an affirming environment where LGBTQIA+ elders and allies can age in community. GenPride, a nonprofit focused on serving LGBTQIA+ seniors, operates a community center on the ground floor of Pride Place that provides specialized programs and services. Special Two-month free rent on select units. Please call for details. Community Features: ◾ Bike storage ◾ Ceiling fans in every unit ◾ Community room ◾ Dishwashers in every unit ◾ Shared outdoor patio Apartment Home Features: Office Hours: Mon - Fri: 8:00 AM - 5:00 PM Phone Number: show contact info Pet Policy: Pets as well as emotional support, companion, and service animals are allowed in all Community Roots Housing buildings. Some restrictions may apply to certain types of pets. Site managers can answer detailed questions about pet restrictions. Pet Fee: 25% first months rent or $300 whichever is lower. Please call our Leasing Office for complete Pet Policy information. Leasing Options: Call Website: www.lease-apts.com?n=pride_place&rp=1Hc7K1nunWsN&t=wb Online Application: www.lease-apts.com?n=pride_place&rp=1Hc7K1nunWsN&t=ap All pricing, availability, fees, and terms are subject to change without notice. EQUAL HOUSING OPPORTUNITY IVC5DZ0015GDN5K",
